Maggot Brain is one of the most influential funk/soul albums of all time, and Funkadelic (spearheaded by band leader George Clinton) were pioneers of the sound.

Erin Toudy – MM Events Maven

Model Milk’s success and longevity is built on the backs of our people, and Erin was easily top of mindfor a staff feature. If you’ve attended or hosted an event in Model Citizen over the last two years, you’ve likely met Erin. 

“Model Citizen is such a beautiful space and there’s so much potential. Every night can be something different than the last and I love that.”

Erin started at Model Milk through our summer of Mega Patio – in fact, it was dining on Mega Patio that sold her on the job. “I was blown away by the quality of food, drinks and the level of service,” she says. Erin continues to add her effervescent personality to our team – through silly cheers at the kitchen pass or the professionalism and care she takes in setting up and hosting each event she runs.

She is the first to admit that she strives to make our spaces as inviting as her own home. “The best part about working at Model is the environment. The staff and guests really make it a great place to be!”

Erin continues to be an immensely valuable asset to the Model Milk team, and we can’t wait to see what she does next!

📷: @mattdavisau

Welcome, Chef Merritt Gordon @merritt_gordon, to the Model Milk kitchen. Chef came from and will continue to oversee @thepigeonholebar, and we're excited for him to join us on this side. Below, we asked him our FAQs.

What is your culinary ethos? Vivimus. Rideat. Amare.
 
What do you like to do when you're not in the building? Getting out with my new puppy, Parker. 

What drew you to Model Milk and Pigeonhole? The chance to contribute to the legacy of talented and dedicated chefs who have called the building home.

Given the short & abrupt seasonality of locally-sourced ingredients, what inspires you about working with food in Alberta? It gives you a chance to appreciate and play with the humbler vegetables, such as cabbage and potatoes, that get us through the winter.

No detail left untouched.
